Agon Terminal - XMODEM / YMODEM
-------------------------------
A simple serial terminal for the Agon Light / Console8 microcomputers, featuring XMODEM and YMODEM file transfer, session capture,
and a full-screen interface with a large 24-line workspace.

Features
--------
    Full Serial Terminal – 115200 8N1 communication (configurable)

    XMODEM File Transfer – Send and receive files using the classic XMODEM protocol (128-byte blocks, CRC/Checksum)

    YMODEM File Transfer – Send and receive files with support for:

        Filename and file size

        1KB blocks for faster transfers

        CRC16 error checking

    Session Capture – Save all serial activity to a file (capture.txt)

    Large Workspace – 24 lines of text area (lines 5–28) for better visibility

    Local Echo Toggle – Enable/disable local echo with Ctrl+E

    Help Screen – Built-in command reference (Ctrl+H)

    Configuration Menu – Toggle between CRC and Checksum for XMODEM (Ctrl+B, then T)

    Clean Interface – Professional layout with status bar and visual feedback

Controls
--------
Key	Function
Ctrl+C	Send file via XMODEM
Ctrl+D	Receive file via XMODEM
Ctrl+Y	Send file via YMODEM (1K blocks, filename support)
Ctrl+U	Receive file via YMODEM
Ctrl+E	Toggle local echo (ON/OFF)
Ctrl+F	Toggle session capture (ON/OFF)
Ctrl+L	Clear screen
Ctrl+H	Show help screen
Ctrl+B	Configuration menu
Ctrl+Q	Exit terminal

Installation
------------
    Copy minicom.bin to your SD card in /bin directory.

    Run from the MOS prompt:

    *minicom

File Transfer
-------------
Sending a File (XMODEM or YMODEM)

    Press Ctrl+C (XMODEM) or Ctrl+Y (YMODEM).

    Enter the filename (e.g., program.bin).

    The terminal will show file size and wait for the receiver.

    Progress is displayed during transfer.

Receiving a File (XMODEM or YMODEM)

    Press Ctrl+D (XMODEM) or Ctrl+U (YMODEM).

    Enter the destination filename.

    The terminal waits for the sender and shows progress.

    Note: YMODEM sends the filename and file size automatically. XMODEM sends raw data only.

Session Capture
---------------
Press Ctrl+F to start or stop capturing all incoming serial data to capture.txt on the SD card.

Configuration
---------------

Press Ctrl+B to open the configuration menu:

    Press T to toggle between CRC (more reliable) and Checksum (faster) for XMODEM transfers.

    Press any other key to exit.

Status Bar
---------------

The status bar (bottom line) shows:

    Baud rate (115200 8N1)
    Local echo status (ON/OFF)
    Capture status (ON/OFF)
    XMODEM mode (CRC / CHK)
    Connection status (YES/NO)

